four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/J/25 Q21","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Work out $2\\dfrac{1}{5} \\times 1\\dfrac{5}{9}$.\nGive your answer as a mixed number in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025MayJune-Paper12-Q22","paper":"2025MayJune-Paper12","qnum":22,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.9","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/J/25 Q22","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The mass, $m$ kg, of a stone is 3.2 kg, correct to the nearest 100 g.\nComplete this statement about the value of $m$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025MayJune-Paper12-Q23","paper":"2025MayJune-Paper12","qnum":23,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/J/25 Q23","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"(a) Factorise.\n$9x - 6xy$\n\n(b) Expand and simplify.\n$(2x + 3)^{2}$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2025MayJune-Paper12-Q24","paper":"2025MayJune-Paper12","qnum":24,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/J/25 Q24","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Solve the simultaneous equations.\n\n$5x + 2y = 3$\n$3x + 4y = 27$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2025MayJune-Paper12-Q25","paper":"2025MayJune-Paper12","qnum":25,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/12/M/J/25 Q25","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The diagram shows a shape made from two different semicircles, with the same centre.\n\n\\beg